he dream alive." Robinson connects the rise of global jihad to other "movements of rage" such as the Nazi Brownshirts, White supremacists, Khmer Rouge, and Boko Haram. Ultimately, he shows that while global jihad has posed a low strategic threat, it has instigated an outsized reaction from the United States and other Western nations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aIslam and politicsxHistoryy20th century. 0aIslam and politicsxHistoryy21st century. 0aIslamic fundamentalismxHistoryy20th century. 0aIslamic fundamentalismxHistoryy21st century. 0aJihadxHistoryy20th century. 0aJihadxHistoryy21st century. 0aPolitical violencexReligious aspectsxIslam. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Terrorism.2bisacsh  aGlobal Jihad.  aISIS.  aIslam.  aIslamic State.  aIslamism.  aJihad.  aJihadism.  aMiddle East.  aMovements of Rage.  aSocial Movements.  aTerrorism.  aal-Qa’ida.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2020z9783110704594oZDB-23-PLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069218140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150361410940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503614109423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503614109.jpg  a978-3-11-069218-1  SUP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070472-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-PLWb